{
  "doc_id": "4391",
  "text": "Lemma D.3. Suppose that F : M → N is a real-analytic map between realanalytic manifolds of equal dimension k, and M is connected. Let M ′ be the closed subset of points x ∈ M at which the Jacobian DF x : T x M → T F (x) N is singular. Then either M = M ′ or M ′ has zero measure in M. Proof. In a local coordinate chart, the defining condition for M ′ is precisely that the determinant of the k × k Jacobian matrix in local coordinates (whose entries are real-analytic functions of the local coordinates) is zero. This set is a real-analytic function of local coordinates. The zero set of a real-analytic function on a connected open subset of R k is either the whole set or a set of measure zero (in fact, by a much deeper result of Lojasiewicz, a finite union of analytic submanifolds of codimension at least 1-see Theorem 6.3.3 of [CITATION_1] ).",
